We started the season intending to be seriously competitive, and it didn't go according to plan. But then we were able to pivot straight into a rebuild situation, with TONS of draft capital and so many options to choose from in deciding what direction the new management wants to take. All within a WEEK. This same process has taken other teams YEARS to get to, years of being in a boring purgatory between team development and true competitive play. And the best part is that the weeks after all this were SO FUN to watch! Even with the insane number of injuries, the remaining veterans and rookies stepped up and put on an amazing show. The energy was incredible and revitalizing and everyone really did a tremendous job. A massive thank you to Poile for all his work these past years, he made the team what they are and his trade decisions this year put them in an INCREDIBLE position for future growth. It's because of him, and the remarkable effort of the team, that the future looks so bright! We have so much to look forward to!!!
